The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 13 November is 100,696 (11,605.8 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 08 November, there were 3,724 new confirmed cases (429.2 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 01 November, there were 4,850 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 23% (1,126 fewer cases).
